---
pagination:
  data: orgs
  size: 1
  alias: org
layout: base.njk
eleventyComputed:
  title: "CMS Walkthrough"
  permalink: "/{{ org.slug }}/walkthrough/"
---

<div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>CMS Walkthrough</h1>
        <p>Step-by-step: draft content with Claude, publish through the CMS, see it live.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<section>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="walkthrough-intro">
            <p>{{ org.walkthrough.intro }}</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section--alt">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Step 1: Draft with Claude</h2>
        <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Open Claude Desktop</h4>
                    <p>Launch the app on your computer. You'll see a chat window.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Copy a prompt from the <a href="/{{ org.slug }}/prompts/">Prompts page</a></h4>
                    <p>Pick the prompt that matches what you're updating. Each prompt tells you which CMS section to use.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Paste, customize, and run</h4>
                    <p>Replace the [brackets] with your real details. Press Enter. Review the output and iterate until you're happy.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="walkthrough-example">
            <h4>Example: Adding a volunteer opportunity</h4>
            <div class="prompt-text" style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">
                <code>{{ org.walkthrough.examplePrompt }}</code>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Step 2: Open the CMS</h2>
        <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Go to <a href="{{ org.cmsUrl }}" target="_blank">{{ org.cmsUrl | replace("https://", "") }}</a></h4>
                    <p>This opens the content manager. If it's your first time, click "Login with GitHub" and authorize access.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Grant org access (first time only)</h4>
                    <p>If this is your first time, GitHub may block CMS writes. Go to <a href="https://github.com/settings/applications" target="_blank">github.com &rarr; Settings &rarr; Applications</a> &rarr; "RFY Website CMS" &rarr; click <strong>"Grant"</strong> next to <strong>thewicksproject</strong>. Then log out of the CMS and log back in.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Find the sidebar</h4>
                    <p>On the left you'll see <strong>Collections</strong> — a list of website sections. These match the CMS paths shown on each prompt.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">CMS Sidebar Sections</h3>
        <p>Here's what you'll see in the sidebar and where each section maps:</p>

        <div class="walkthrough-table">
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Sidebar Section</th>
                        <th>What's Inside</th>
                        <th>Website Page</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    {% for section in org.walkthrough.cmsSections %}
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>{{ section.name }}</strong></td>
                        <td>{{ section.contents }}</td>
                        <td>{{ section.page }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    {% endfor %}
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section--alt">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Step 3: Navigate and Edit</h2>

        <div class="walkthrough-demo">
            <h3>Example: Volunteer Page &rarr; Volunteer Opportunities</h3>
            <div class="steps">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-num">1</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h4>Click "Volunteer Page" in the sidebar</h4>
                        <p>You'll see one entry: <strong>Volunteer Opportunities</strong>. Click it.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-num">2</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h4>See the current entries</h4>
                        <p>The form shows all existing volunteer roles as collapsible cards. A preview panel on the right shows how the data looks.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-num">3</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h4>Click "Add opportunities +"</h4>
                        <p>A new blank card appears at the bottom. Expand it by clicking the arrow.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-num">4</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h4>Paste Claude's output</h4>
                        <p>Fill in the <strong>Title</strong> field (e.g., "Youth Workshop Facilitator"). Then add each detail bullet as a separate <strong>Detail</strong> entry using the "Add details +" button.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem; color: var(--steel-blue); font-size: 0.95rem;">
            <strong>Other sections work the same way</strong> — find the section in the sidebar, click the entry, edit the fields, and publish. The button labels change (e.g., "Add stat +" for Statistics), but the pattern is identical.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Step 4: Publish</h2>
        <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Review your changes</h4>
                    <p>Check the preview panel on the right side. Make sure everything looks right.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Click the green "Publish" button</h4>
                    <p>It's at the top of the page. A dropdown appears — click <strong>"Publish now"</strong>. You'll see "CHANGES SAVED" confirm the publish.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section--alt">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Step 5: See It Live</h2>
        <div class="steps">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Wait 30-60 seconds</h4>
                    <p>The website rebuilds automatically after you publish.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Open <a href="{{ org.siteUrl }}" target="_blank">{{ org.siteUrl | replace("https://", "") }}</a></h4>
                    <p>Navigate to the page you updated. Do a hard refresh (<strong>Cmd+Shift+R</strong> on Mac, <strong>Ctrl+Shift+R</strong> on Windows) to see the latest version.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Verify your changes</h4>
                    <p>Your new content should appear on the live site. If it doesn't show up after 60 seconds, try hard-refreshing again.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
        <div class="tips-grid">
            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-badge" style="background: #FFEBEE; color: #C62828;">!</div>
                <h4>CMS won't load</h4>
                <p>Try Chrome (works best). Clear cache and try again. Try incognito mode.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-badge" style="background: #FFEBEE; color: #C62828;">!</div>
                <h4>GitHub login fails</h4>
                <p>Make sure you accepted the collaborator invitation email. Check spam folder.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-badge" style="background: #FFEBEE; color: #C62828;">!</div>
                <h4>Changes not showing</h4>
                <p>Wait 60 seconds. Hard refresh (Cmd+Shift+R). If still nothing, ask Victor.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-badge" style="background: #FFEBEE; color: #C62828;">!</div>
                <h4>Published wrong content</h4>
                <p>Don't worry — Victor can revert any change. Just let him know.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tip-card">
                <div class="tip-badge" style="background: #FFEBEE; color: #C62828;">!</div>
                <h4>Publish fails or read-only</h4>
                <p>Go to <a href="https://github.com/settings/applications" target="_blank">GitHub Settings &rarr; Applications</a> &rarr; "RFY Website CMS" &rarr; click <strong>"Grant"</strong> for thewicksproject. Log out and back in.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

{% if org.walkthrough.verificationChecks %}
<section class="section--alt">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Verification Log</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--steel-blue); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Pre-training verification completed {{ org.walkthrough.verificationDate }}.</p>

        <div class="walkthrough-table">
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Check</th>
                        <th>Result</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    {% for item in org.walkthrough.verificationChecks %}
                    <tr>
                        <td>{{ item.check }}</td>
                        <td>{{ item.result }}</td>
                    </tr>
                    {% endfor %}
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
{% endif %}
